The Devil In The White City|Erik Larson|Vintage|A story of how an architect and a serial killer were linked by the Chicago World's Fair of 1893. Originally published in 2003.
Just Mercy|Bryan Stevenson|Spiegel & Grau|A law professor and MacArthur grant recipient's memoir of his decades of work to free innocent people condemned to death. Originally published in 2014.
Filthy Rich|James Patterson,John Connolly with Tim Malloy|Little, Brown|The story of a South Florida financier convicted of soliciting sex from underage girls.
My Own Words|Ruth Bader Ginsburg with Mary Hartnett,Wendy W. Williams|Simon & Schuster|A collection of articles and speeches by the Supreme Court justice.
Notorious Rbg|Irin Carmon,Shana Knizhnik|Dey Street/Morrow|A celebration of the life and career of the Supreme Court justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg.
The Midnight Assassin|Skip Hollandsworth|Holt|The hunt for America's first serial killer in Austin, Tex., in 1885.
Adnan'S Story|Rabia Chaudry|St. Martin's|A friend of Adnan Syed, whose murder case was the focus of the popular podcast “Serial,” maintains his innocence.
Orange Is The New Black|Piper Kerman|Spiegel & Grau|A memoir about a year in a women’s prison; the basis for the Netflix series. Originally published in 2010.
Red Notice|Bill Browder|Simon & Schuster|A successful American hedge fund manager in Russia was expelled by kleptocrats who then seized his property.
Sisters In Law|Linda Hirshman|Harper/HarperCollins|The contrasting careers of the Supreme Court justices Sandra Day O'Connor and Ruth Bader Ginsburg.
